# Job Hunt Workspace

Generated by `job-hunt-toolkit:init-workspace`. Regenerate by re-running the skill — do not edit by hand, or your changes will be overwritten on the next init.

## Layout

```
./
├── {{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_{{ROLE}}_CV.html   # master source (edit this)
├── {{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_{{ROLE}}_CV.pdf    # master export (regenerate from HTML)
├── README.md
├── AGENTS.md
├── NAMING.md
├── .gitignore
└── <company>/                             # one folder per application
    ├── company.md
    ├── job_description.md                 # or .<ext> with original extension when user supplies a file
    ├── {{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_<Role>_CV.html
    └── {{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_<Role>_CV.pdf
```

## Workflow

1. `/job-hunt-toolkit:new-application <company-slug>` — start a new application
2. `/job-hunt-toolkit:export-pdf` — regenerate any PDF from its HTML source
3. `/job-hunt-toolkit:prepare-to-send` — run the pre-send checklist before attaching

## Master CV

`{{FIRST}}_{{LAST}}_{{ROLE}}_CV.html` is the **canonical source**. All edits happen here. The `.pdf` is a regeneratable export.

Never overwrite the master with a tailored variant. Tailored versions live inside `<company>/`.

## Rules

See `AGENTS.md` and `NAMING.md`. The authoritative versions live in the plugin; these are generated snapshots.
